                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor (?); some lines on the incipit page, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each sub-section of tText I; the words: ʿadi (fol. 6rc), kǝfl (e.g., fols. 41rb, 62vc, 63rc), fǝkkare (e.g., fols. 136ra, 137ra, 139rc), śalǝs (e.g., fols. 137rc, 138rb, 139rc), yǝbe (e.g., fols.147ra, 147vb, 148ra); elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="153vb"/>Fol. 153vb: በአኰቴተ᎓ እግዚአብሔር᎓ ተጽሕፈ᎓ ሃይማኖተ᎓ አበው᎓ ቅዱሳን᎓ በመዋዕለ᎓ ንጉሥነ᎓ መፍቀሬ᎓ እግዚአብሔር᎓ [vac] ዘተጸውዓ᎓ በጸጋ᎓ ጥምቀት᎓ በከመ᎓ ሰማዕት᎓ [vac] በረድኤተ᎓ ቅዱስ᎓ [vac] ወበአስተሐምሞታ᎓ ለነዳይት᎓ [vac] ወተፈጸመ᎓ እምአመ᎓ ነግሠ᎓ በ፳ወ፰ዓመት᎓ በዘመነ᎓ ዮሐንስ᎓ ወንጌላዊ᎓ ወአሜሃ᎓ ኮነ᎓ ዓመተ᎓ ምሕረት᎓ ፸፻ወ፩፻፶ወ፪᎓ ባሕቱ᎓ ፈጣሬ᎓ ዓለማት᎓ ያኑኅ᎓ መዋዕሊሁ᎓ ለንጉሥነ᎓ ዳግማይ᎓ ቈስጠንጢኖስ᎓ ዘሐደሳ᎓ ለብልየተ᎓ ዓለም᎓ በርትዕት᎓ ሃይማኖት᎓ ወይዕቀቦ᎓ ከመ᎓ ብንተ᎓ ዓይን᎓ &lt;…&gt; <foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 153vb: By the glory of God, the faith of the righteous fathers was written during the reign of our king lover of God [vac] who was named by the grace of baptism, according to witnesses, ... by the help of St. ... and by the care of poor .... It was completed on the 28th year from the time he became king, during the year of John the evangelist. At that time the year of mercy was 7152. Moreover the creator of the world may prolong the age of our king Constantine II, who renewed the oldness of the world with the Orthodox faith. May He protect him like the pupil.
</foreign>
                        <note>Given and baptismal names of the king, and other names are skipped in the colophon.</note>
                     </colophon>
